{"id": "4512", "post": "<div class=\"post-4512 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-tutorials tag-tutorials-2\" id=\"post-4512\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/handle-dns-properly-with-cpanel/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Handle DNS properly with cPanel</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/tutorials-2/\" rel=\"tag\">tutorials</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> October 19, 2013 @ 12:15 am, by Maarten Kossen</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3957 litespeed-loaded\" alt=\"lowendtutorial\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/lowendtutorial.png.webp\" width=\"271\" height=\"70\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>After a couple of very busy weeks (<a href=\"https://scontent-a.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ash3/935943_604239752951090_795338313_n.jpg\">got married</a>, <a href=\"https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash3/1410674_10151927702379752_1623313358_o.jpg\">went on our honeymoon</a> and <a href=\"http://lowendtalk.com/discussion/14580/radio-silence#latest\">took over from Liam</a>) it\u2019s finally time for a tutorial again! The tutorials are going to be released in a more natural flow now. Saturday will not always be tutorial day any longer.</p><p>So, on-topic! cPanel is a well-known, almost de-facto standard, hosting control panel. Most shared hosting providers use it, but it\u2019s also popular amongst people that either want to run their own server but don\u2019t have the technical knowledge to do everything on the CLI or by people that want to give people they know easy shared hosting.&nbsp; With special pricing for VPS, a cPanel license costs about $15. If you\u2019re lucky, your provider can even provide it to you cheaper. The cheapest I have personally seen is $17, for a full 2GB VPS with cPanel included (that\u2019s $10 for the cPanel license)!</p><p><span id=\"more-4512\"></span></p><p>But, by using cPanel, a new problem arises: the need for DNS. cPanel includes BIND and other DNS software, but single cPanel user with DNS is a single point of failure. So, the natural choice would be to buy a second server and install cPanel or cPanel DNSONLY. But, with just one secondary DNS server, some other issues may arise: the primary of your cPanel server (which is often used for shared hosting) can get \u201ctainted\u201d and when you want to move your cPanel server, it includes moving your primary DNS as well. All in all, not an ideal combination.</p><p>So, my solution to this problem is as follows: get two small VPS and install cPanel DNSONLY on both of them. Then, you get have any number of cPanel servers send over the records to them and you\u2019ve basically got a dedicated DNS cluster. Of course, you can use more than 2 DNS servers (3 is often a recommended minimum). But two is quite common and shouldn\u2019t have to cost too much.</p><p>You don\u2019t need heavy hardware for a DNS server. A 128MB VPS should me sufficient for a small to medium DNS cluster. There\u2019s plenty of offers with annual deals for those, so you can get two of such machine for as little as $20-$30/year.</p><p>Anyway, on to the good stuff: the installation!</p><h2>Installing cPanel DNSONLY</h2><p>cPanel DNSONLY is free and it\u2019s easy to install. It does require CentOS. I would recommend using CentOS 6. A clean install is also recommended.</p><p>To download cPanel DNSONLY, run:</p><blockquote><p>wget http://httpupdate.cpanel.net/latest-dnsonly</p></blockquote><p>This should download the installer. It\u2019s quite small. Now, make it executable:</p><blockquote><p>chmod +x latest-dnsonly</p></blockquote><p>And execute it:</p><blockquote><p>./latest-dnsonly</p></blockquote><p>This should run the installer and it should look like this:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023-300x191.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4521 litespeed-loaded\" alt=\"root@cpns1_023\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023-300x191.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"191\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023-300x191.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023.png.webp 724w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023-300x191.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/root@cpns1_023.png.webp 724w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>Let it run, grab a cup of coffee, walk you dog, go grocery shopping. When you\u2019re back, grab a beer. It should be done by then! Jokes aside: it could take 20-30 minutes depending on the speed of the VPS. Once it\u2019s done, open up your browser and surf to https://YOURIP:2087. This should open the login screen of cPanel.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WHM-Login-2013-10-14-08-28-02.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4523\" alt=\"WHM-Login 2013-10-14 08-28-02\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WHM-Login-2013-10-14-08-28-02-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WHM-Login-2013-10-14-08-28-02-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WHM-Login-2013-10-14-08-28-02-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WHM-Login-2013-10-14-08-28-02.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Log in with your root account, which should send you to the setup process.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-29-07.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4525\" alt=\"Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7 2013-10-14 08-29-07\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-29-07-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-29-07-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-29-07-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-29-07.png 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>First up is accepting the license agreement. Please <strong>read</strong> this, even though it\u2019s boring. Just like Terms of Service, there\u2019s stuff in there that <em>could</em> be important. Once you find out is actually <em>is</em> important, it\u2019s usually to late. So better read it upfront ;-)</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-32-20.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyMzMiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMjMzIDMwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4527\" alt=\"Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7 2013-10-14 08-32-20\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-32-20-233x300.png.webp\" width=\"233\" height=\"300\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-32-20-233x300.png.webp 233w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-32-20-798x1024.png.webp 798w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-32-20.png.webp 1190w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 233px) 100vw, 233px\"></a></p><p>Next up is some basic configuration and networking setup. Two things that you have to fill out here:</p><ul><li>Server Contact E-mail Address: this is where cPanel sends notifications, logs, etc.</li><li>This Server\u2019s Hostname: the hostname of this server</li></ul><p>The resolvers should have been filled automatically. If not, find out what your resolvers are and fill out those fields.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-33-54.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4529\" alt=\"Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7 2013-10-14 08-33-54\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-33-54-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-33-54-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-33-54-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-33-54.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Next, it fives you an overview of IP addresses your server has. Usually it\u2019s just the one and cPanel will use that. Otherwise, you can choose.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-34-42.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyMTEiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMjExIDMwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4531\" alt=\"Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7 2013-10-14 08-34-42\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-34-42-211x300.png.webp\" width=\"211\" height=\"300\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-34-42-211x300.png.webp 211w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-34-42-723x1024.png.webp 723w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Web-Host-Manager-11-38-2-7-2013-10-14-08-34-42.png.webp 1190w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 211px) 100vw, 211px\"></a></p><p>Final step is the name server software selection and configuration. I usually go for BIND here, because it\u2019s the default. I advise you to do the same. Fill out the name servers this server will use (usually the hostname of this server and the hostname of your other DNS server). Optionally, you can add A records for this domain. If you\u2019re planning to use this server as the DNS for the hostname\u2019s domain name, you should do this.</p><p>That\u2019s it! Click \u2018Finished Setup Wizard\u2019 and you\u2019ll be sent to the WHM interface.</p><h2>Configure cPanel DNSONLY</h2><p>Now everything is set up, let\u2019s configure this server as a DNS server for a cPanel server. From the WHM interface, click on \u2018Cluster/Remote Access\u2019 and \u2018Setup Remote Access Key\u2019. Click \u2018Generate new key\u2019 and copy the entire key.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-38-06.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4533\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpns1 2013-10-14 08-38-06\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-38-06-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-38-06-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-38-06-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-38-06.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Now, head over to your cPanel server and go to \u2018Cluster/Remote Access\u2019 and click on \u2018Configure Cluster\u2019. Under \u2018Modify Cluster Status\u2019 (which should be disabled) you should click the \u2018Enable\u2019 radio button and click \u2018Change\u2019. This should enable the DNS clustering.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-27.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4535\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpanel 2013-10-14 08-40-27\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-27-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-27-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-27-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-27.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Now, scroll down. Under \u2018Add a new server to the cluster\u2019 you can add a new server. The \u2018Backend Type\u2019 should remain cPanel. Click \u2018Configure\u2019.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-50.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4537\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpanel 2013-10-14 08-40-50\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-50-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-50-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-50-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-40-50.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>This should open up a new window where you can fill out the details for the new server. Start by filling out the hostname, the username (root) and paste the remote access key we\u2019ve just copied into the field \u201cRemove server access hash\u201d.&nbsp;Also check the box \u201cSetup Reverse Trust Relationship\u201d.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-11.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4539\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpanel 2013-10-14 08-56-11\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-11-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-11-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-11-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-11.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Scroll down again. There should be a select box \u201cDNS Role\u201d. Select \u201cWrite-only\u201d here. You do not want to synchronize the changes, but you want changes from your cPanel server to be sent to the DNS server. Not the other way around.</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-04.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4541\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpanel 2013-10-14 08-56-04\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-04-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-04-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-04-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpanel-2013-10-14-08-56-04.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>Finally, click \u2018Submit\u2019. You\u2019ll get a confirmation message telling you everything has been set up! To check this, go do \u201cConfigure Cluster\u201d once more and confirm that everything is good:</p><p><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-56-52.png\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4543\" alt=\"WebHost-Manager-cpns1 2013-10-14 08-56-52\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-56-52-300x200.png.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-56-52-300x200.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-56-52-1024x686.png.webp 1024w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/WebHost-Manager-cpns1-2013-10-14-08-56-52.png.webp 1203w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></a></p><p>And you\u2019re all done! You should do this for your second DNS server exactly the same way. Once you\u2019re done with that, you\u2019ve got a cPanel server with two independent DNS servers!</p><h2>Final notes</h2><p>There\u2019s various other configuration options to set up a DNS cluster with cPanel. For instance, you can also use several full cPanel servers with multiple IPs for your DNS cluster. However, the solution of this tutorial is one of the fastest ones in replication terms and gives you most flexibility. Enjoy cPanel!</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Up next time</span>: getting started with OpenVZ!</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhandle-dns-properly-with-cpanel%2F&amp;t=Handle%20DNS%20properly%20with%20cPanel\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Handle%20DNS%20properly%20with%20cPanel&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhandle-dns-properly-with-cpanel%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetwork\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-twitter dpsp-no-label\" title=\"Share on Twitter\"><span class=\"dpsp-netw